 The All Progressives Congress (APC) in Osun State has mourned the death of the Chairman of Olorunda-North Local Council Development Area (LCDA), Alhaji Quadri Owonikoko. He died early yesterday. A statement by the Chairman of the party, Mr. Gboyega Famodun, described the death of Owonikoko as shocking.  He said: “Owonikoko was a loyal party man. On behalf of my family and the state executive members of our party, I share in the grief and pray fervently to God to forgive his sins. May God Almighty grant his family, party members and leaders, relations and well-wishers the fortitude to bear the irreparable loss.”